---
import LandingPageLayout from '../layouts/LandingPageLayout.astro';

const title = "Free Calorie Counter App - Count Calories for Weight Loss";
const description = "Free calorie counter with barcode scanning, 220,000+ foods, AI food logging, and automatic goals. Complete guide to counting calories for weight loss. No account required.";
const keywords = "calorie counter, free calorie counter, how to count calories, calorie counting, calorie counter app, count calories, calorie tracking, calorie deficit";
---

<LandingPageLayout title={title} description={description} keywords={keywords}>

  <!-- Hero copy -->
  <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-50 via-emerald-50/30 to-gray-50 dark:from-gray-900 dark:via-gray-800 dark:to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 pt-6 md:pt-8 pb-10 text-center">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-700 text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400 text-sm font-medium px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-6">
        100% free · No account required
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">The Best <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Free Calorie Counter</span></h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Barcode scanning, macro tracking, and AI food logging — <span class="font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">completely free, no account or subscription required.</span>
      </p>
      <a
        href="/?from=landing-page"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 hover:from-emerald-600 hover:to-teal-600 text-white font-bold text-lg py-4 px-12 rounded-xl shadow-lg shadow-emerald-500/30 hover:shadow-xl hover:shadow-emerald-500/40 transition-all active:scale-95 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-emerald-300"
      >
        Start Counting Calories Now →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Hero image -->
  <div class="bg-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-950">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
      <picture>
        <source srcset="/hero-screenshot.webp" type="image/webp" media="(min-width: 768px)" />
        <source srcset="/hero-mobile.webp" type="image/webp" media="(max-width: 767px)" />
        <img
          src="/hero-screenshot.webp"
          alt="Free Calorie Track calorie counter showing daily calorie progress and food log"
          width="5000"
          height="3000"
          class="w-full h-auto"
          loading="eager"
          style="image-rendering: high-quality; transform: translateZ(0); will-change: transform;"
        />
      </picture>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Value Props -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent">No cost. No catch.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Every feature is free — barcode scanning, macro tracking, AI food logging, weekly coaching, trends. No premium tier, no trial that expires, no ads. Free Calorie Track is funded by optional donations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent">No account. No cloud.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Your data lives on your device, not on a server. There's nothing to sign up for, no email required, and nothing to hand over.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Works everywhere, even offline.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">Install to your home screen from any browser — iPhone, Android, desktop. Runs like a native app and works without internet.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Features Grid -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center mb-2"><span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-teal-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Free Calorie Counter</span><span class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100"> key features</span></h2>
      <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">Everything you want. No paywalls.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-4">

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M8.5 14.5A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 11 12c0-1.38-.5-2-1-3-1.072-2.143-.224-4.054 2-6 .5 2.5 2 4.9 4 6.5 2 1.6 3 3.5 3 5.5a7 7 0 1 1-14 0c0-1.153.433-2.294 1-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 0 2.5 2.5z"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Calorie & macro tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Log meals with real-time totals. Track protein, carbs, and fat with auto-calculated goals or set your own.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M7 21h10"/><path d="M12 21a9 9 0 0 0 9-9H3a9 9 0 0 0 9 9Z"/><path d="M11.38 12a2.4 2.4 0 0 1-.4-4.77 2.4 2.4 0 0 1 3.2-3.19 2.4 2.4 0 0 1 3.47-.63 2.4 2.4 0 0 1 3.37 3.37 2.4 2.4 0 0 1-1.1 3.7 2.51 2.51 0 0 1 .03 1.1"/><path d="m13 12 4-4"/><path d="M10.9 7.25A3.99 3.99 0 0 0 4 10c0 .73.2 1.41.54 2"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Nutrition tracking</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Optionally track fiber, sodium, sugar, and saturated fat for a fuller picture of your diet.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M3 7V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h2"/><path d="M17 3h2a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v2"/><path d="M21 17v2a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-2"/><path d="M7 21H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-2"/><path d="M8 7v10"/><path d="M12 7v10"/><path d="M17 7v10"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Barcode scanning</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Scan any product instantly. 220,000+ items in the database. Free, no daily limit.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Exercise logging</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">250+ exercises across cardio, strength, and sports. MET-based calorie burn calculations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Trends & insights</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Weekly averages, weight charts, and 7-day rolling averages to see the real picture.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="m12 3-1.912 5.813a2 2 0 0 1-1.275 1.275L3 12l5.813 1.912a2 2 0 0 1 1.275 1.275L12 21l1.912-5.813a2 2 0 0 1 1.275-1.275L21 12l-5.813-1.912a2 2 0 0 1-1.275-1.275L12 3Z"/><path d="M5 3v4"/><path d="M19 17v4"/><path d="M3 5h4"/><path d="M17 19h4"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">AI food logging (Beta)</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Describe a meal, snap a photo, or photograph a recipe — AI estimates calories instantly. 10 free logs/day.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M12 5a3 3 0 1 0-5.997.125 4 4 0 0 0-2.526 5.77 4 4 0 0 0 .556 6.588A4 4 0 1 0 12 18Z"/><path d="M12 5a3 3 0 1 1 5.997.125 4 4 0 0 1 2.526 5.77 4 4 0 0 1-.556 6.588A4 4 0 1 1 12 18Z"/><path d="M15 13a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-3-4 4.5 4.5 0 0 1-3 4"/><path d="M17.599 6.5a3 3 0 0 0 .399-1.375"/><path d="M6.003 5.125A3 3 0 0 0 6.401 6.5"/><path d="M3.477 10.896a4 4 0 0 1 .585-.396"/><path d="M19.938 10.5a4 4 0 0 1 .585.396"/><path d="M6 18a4 4 0 0 1-1.967-.516"/><path d="M19.967 17.484A4 4 0 0 1 18 18"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Nutrition Coach (Beta)</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Log 3+ days and get a weekly AI analysis of what's working, what to adjust, and what to try. Free and optional.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M12 20h.01"/><path d="M8.5 16.429a5 5 0 0 1 7 0"/><path d="M5 12.859a10 10 0 0 1 5.17-2.69"/><path d="M19 12.859a10 10 0 0 0-2.007-1.523"/><path d="M2 8.82a15 15 0 0 1 4.177-2.643"/><path d="M22 8.82a15 15 0 0 0-11.288-3.764"/><line x1="2" x2="22" y1="2" y2="22"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Works offline</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Install on any device. No internet needed after setup. All data stored locally.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Private by design</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">No account, no subscription, no setup. Your data stays on your device and never passes through our servers.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 9-9 9.75 9.75 0 0 0-6.74 2.74L3 8"/><path d="M3 3v5h5"/><path d="M12 7v5l4 2"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">Editable history</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1 leading-relaxed">Forgot to log yesterday? No problem. Add or edit meals and exercise from any past day.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Guide transition band -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 border-y border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 py-10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">The Guide</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-3">How to Count Calories</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Everything you need to start tracking, stay consistent, and actually see results.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Guide content -->
  <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <!-- Why Count Calories -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Why Count Calories?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Weight management comes down to energy balance. Calorie counting removes the guesswork — instead of wondering why the scale isn't moving, you have data showing exactly what's happening.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border-2 border-red-200 dark:border-red-800 text-center">
          <p class="font-bold text-red-700 dark:text-red-400 mb-1">Eat more than you burn</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">= Weight gain</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border-2 border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 text-center">
          <p class="font-bold text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-1">Eat less than you burn</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">= Weight loss</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border-2 border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 text-center">
          <p class="font-bold text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 mb-1">Eat the same as you burn</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">= Maintenance</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="M2 12s3-7 10-7 10 7 10 7-3 7-10 7-10-7-10-7Z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Creates awareness</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Most people underestimate their intake by 30–50%. Tracking reveals the truth about portion sizes and hidden calories in oils, dressings, and drinks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Flexible eating</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">No foods are off-limits. Fit anything into your daily calorie budget instead of following rigid diet rules that leave no room for real life.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="M15 14c.2-1 .7-1.7 1.5-2.5 1-.9 1.5-2.2 1.5-3.5A6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .2 2.2 1.5 3.5.7.7 1.3 1.5 1.5 2.5"/><path d="M9 18h6"/><path d="M10 22h4"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Based on science</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Weight loss requires a calorie deficit. Counting ensures you're actually eating less than you burn, not just guessing — and lets you verify it's working.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"/><polyline points="16 7 22 7 22 13"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Measurable progress</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Tracking lets you see patterns, identify what's stalling you, and make data-driven adjustments instead of guessing what's wrong.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- How to Count: Step by Step -->
    <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">How to Count Calories: Step by Step</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Calculate your calorie target</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Your TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure) is how many calories you burn per day. Free Calorie Track calculates it automatically from your age, sex, height, weight, and activity level. For weight loss, subtract 300–500 calories. For muscle gain, add 200–300.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Track everything for one baseline week</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Don't change your eating habits yet. Just track everything you normally eat for 7 days. This shows you your current average intake, where most of your calories come from, and your eating patterns — information you can't get any other way.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Weigh your food in grams</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">A digital food scale is the single most important tool for accurate tracking. Place a bowl on the scale, zero it out, then add your food. Weigh calorie-dense items (nuts, oils, cheese, peanut butter) every time — a "tablespoon" of peanut butter eyeballed can easily be 200+ calories instead of 95.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Log everything — including oils and drinks</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Track all meals, snacks, cooking oils, condiments, and drinks (except water, black coffee, and unsweetened tea). Don't wait until the end of the day — log meals as you eat them so nothing gets forgotten.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">5</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Use AI for meals that are hard to log manually</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Restaurant plates, homemade dishes, and recipes from a cookbook don't have barcodes. Instead, snap a photo of the meal or recipe, or just describe it in a few words ("grilled salmon with rice and veggies, about a fist-sized portion"). Free Calorie Track's AI estimates calories and macros instantly and logs it — no database searching required.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">6</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Review weekly and adjust</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Weigh yourself once a week at the same time. If you're not losing 0.5–1 lb per week, reduce calories by 100–200. If you're losing more than 2 lbs/week, increase slightly to preserve muscle. As you lose weight, your TDEE drops — recalculate every 10–15 lbs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Reading Nutrition Labels -->
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">How to Read a Nutrition Label</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Every packaged food has a Nutrition Facts label. Here's what to actually pay attention to.</p>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Serving size (top of label)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Everything else on the label is per this amount. A bag of chips might say "150 calories per serving" but contain 2.5 servings — that's 375 calories for the whole bag. Always check how many servings are in the package, not just the per-serving number.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Calories (the number you track)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">The big bold number. If the label says 180 calories per 40g serving and you weighed 65g, your actual intake is: (65 ÷ 40) × 180 = <strong>293 calories</strong>. Tracking apps do this math automatically when you enter the weight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Macronutrients (optional but useful)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Protein, carbohydrates, and fat. At minimum, track protein — it helps preserve muscle during weight loss and keeps you full. Carbs and fat matter more for specific dietary goals like keto or athletic performance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-xl p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300"><strong>Watch out for:</strong> Unrealistically small serving sizes ("who eats exactly 15 chips?"), "low calorie" claims for tiny portions, and multi-serving packages that look like single servings. When using Free Calorie Track's barcode scanner, all this data is pre-filled — just enter your actual weight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Raw vs Cooked Weight -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Raw vs. Cooked Weight: A Common Mistake</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Food weight changes significantly during cooking. Using the wrong weight is one of the most common tracking errors.</p>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M14 14.76V3.5a2.5 2.5 0 0 0-5 0v11.26a4.5 4.5 0 1 0 5 0z"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400">Meat loses water when cooked</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">100g raw chicken breast ≠ 100g cooked chicken breast. The cooked version is denser and has more calories per gram because the water cooked off.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Rule: Weigh raw when possible. If you weigh cooked, search for "chicken breast cooked" in the app — not the raw entry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M7 16.3c2.2 0 4-1.83 4-4.05 0-1.16-.57-2.26-1.71-3.19S7.29 6.75 7 5.3c-.29 1.45-1.14 2.84-2.29 3.76S3 11.1 3 12.25c0 2.22 1.8 4.05 4 4.05z"/><path d="M12.56 6.6A10.97 10.97 0 0 0 14 3.02c.5 2.5 2 4.9 4 6.5s3 3.5 3 5.5a6.98 6.98 0 0 1-11.91 4.97"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400">Pasta and rice absorb water</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">100g dry oats becomes ~250g cooked. 100g dry pasta becomes ~240g cooked. The calories don't change — the water weight does.</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Rule: Log dry/uncooked weight, or search specifically for "cooked" entries which account for water absorption.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 mt-4 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-700">
        <p class="text-sm text-emerald-800 dark:text-emerald-300 text-center"><strong>Bottom line:</strong> Pick one method (raw or cooked) and stick with it consistently. Mixing them in the same meal is what leads to large errors.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tracking Homemade Meals -->
    <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">How to Track Homemade Meals</h2>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-emerald-300 dark:border-emerald-600 shadow-sm mb-6">
