    <!-- Easy vs Hard Foods -->
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Easy vs. Hard Foods to Track</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border border-emerald-100 dark:border-emerald-800">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-400">Easy to track accurately</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span> Packaged foods with barcodes — scan and done</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span> Whole foods: apple, banana, plain chicken, rice</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span> Chain restaurants — most post nutrition info online</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span> Standard portioned foods: 1 egg, 1 slice of bread</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✓</span> Protein shakes and supplements with labels</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 rounded-xl p-5 border border-amber-100 dark:border-amber-800">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">Harder — but still doable</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">!</span> Independent restaurant meals — estimate conservatively, add ~20%</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">!</span> Mixed dishes (stews, casseroles) — use recipe builder</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">!</span> Nuts, granola, dried fruit — always weigh, never eyeball</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">!</span> Food cooked by others — ask for ingredients or estimate</li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-500 font-bold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">!</span> Restaurant salads — often 800–1,200 calories with dressing</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700 rounded-xl p-4 mt-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-center"><strong>When in doubt:</strong> Overestimate by 10–20%. Consistently overestimating slightly is far better than consistently underestimating, which stalls weight loss without explanation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Eating Out -->
