          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/><path d="m21 21-4.3-4.3"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Look it up first</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Most chain restaurants publish full nutrition info online or in the app. Search the restaurant name in Free Calorie Track before you order.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="m12.83 2.18a2 2 0 0 0-1.66 0L2.6 6.08a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.83l8.58 3.91a2 2 0 0 0 1.66 0l8.58-3.9a1 1 0 0 0 0-1.83Z"/><path d="m22 17.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 17.65"/><path d="m22 12.65-9.17 4.16a2 2 0 0 1-1.66 0L2 12.65"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Build it from components</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Log individual parts: bun (200), patty (300), cheese (100), sauce (50), fries (400) = 1,050 calories. More accurate than finding a generic "burger" entry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="m3 16 4 4 4-4"/><path d="M7 20V4"/><path d="m21 8-4-4-4 4"/><path d="M17 4v16"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Find a comparable entry</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Search for similar dishes from comparable restaurants. A chicken sandwich from one major chain is usually within 10–15% of another.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="M12 8v4"/><path d="M12 16h.01"/></svg>
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Add a buffer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Restaurant portions are cooked in more oil than you'd use at home. Add 15–20% to your estimate to account for hidden cooking fats and larger portions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-700 flex items-start gap-4 mt-2">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m12 3-1.912 5.813a2 2 0 0 1-1.275 1.275L3 12l5.813 1.912a2 2 0 0 1 1.275 1.275L12 21l1.912-5.813a2 2 0 0 1 1.275-1.275L21 12l-5.813-1.912a2 2 0 0 1-1.275-1.275L12 3Z"/><path d="M5 3v4"/><path d="M19 17v4"/><path d="M3 5h4"/><path d="M17 19h4"/></svg>
        <div>
          <p class="font-bold mb-1">Easier: snap a photo or describe the meal with AI</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">At any restaurant, open the AI logging feature in Free Calorie Track and either snap a photo of your plate or type what you ordered. The AI estimates calories and macros instantly and logs it directly — no searching, no component math. 10 free logs per day.</p>
