    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Common Calorie Counting Mistakes</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-amber-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Not weighing calorie-dense foods</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">You think: 1 tablespoon of peanut butter (95 cal). You actually use: 2+ tablespoons (200+ cal). That 100-calorie daily error adds up to 700+ calories a week — enough to stall weight loss completely. Always weigh nuts, oils, cheese, nut butters, and dried fruit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-amber-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Forgetting cooking oils</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">1 tablespoon of olive oil = 120 calories. Cook with 2–3 tablespoons per meal and that's 240–360 untracked calories daily. Measure oils with a spoon or pour them onto the scale. It takes 5 seconds.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-amber-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Not tracking on weekends</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">The math is brutal: 500 cal deficit Mon–Fri = 2,500 cal deficit. Then 1,000 cal surplus Sat–Sun = 2,000 surplus. Net weekly deficit: only 500 calories — 0.14 lbs lost instead of 0.7 lbs. Track every day, or plan your weekends deliberately.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-amber-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Mixing raw and cooked weights</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Logging 200g raw chicken but searching "chicken breast cooked" (or vice versa) can cause a 30–40% calorie error. Pick one convention and stick to it. Raw is usually easier since you weigh before cooking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-amber-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3z"/><path d="M12 9v4"/><path d="M12 17h.01"/></svg>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-1">Not adjusting as you lose weight</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">A 200-lb person burns more calories at rest than a 160-lb person. As you lose weight, your TDEE drops. If your weight loss stalls for 3+ weeks without explanation, recalculate your TDEE and reduce your target slightly.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Tips for Making It Stick</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><path d="M8 2v4"/><path d="M16 2v4"/><rect width="18" height="18" x="3" y="4" rx="2"/><path d="M3 10h18"/></svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Pre-log your day in the morning</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 text-sm">Plan and log all three meals first thing. You'll see how many calories remain for snacks, which prevents decision fatigue later. It takes 2–3 minutes and removes the guesswork from the whole day.</p>
            </div>
